{"TopicId":151407,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Sun tracking","CreatedByName":"Jimbodiah","CreatedById":152759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T14:04:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jimbodiah","CreatedById":152759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T14:04:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi Guys,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any mod out there that allows for a station/satellite to constantly face the sun, like some part you put on that will use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E to keep facing one direction?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Theysen","CreatedById":144656,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T14:12:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/102277-12-persistentrotation-181/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EPersistent Rotation\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0can help you do so \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jimbodiah","CreatedById":152759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T19:40:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve tried hat, but it only keeps the ship in the same position to a relative body. It does not actively turn the vessel towards it from a certain part\u0027s perspective.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T20:14:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222836992\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151407\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478202039\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jimbodiah\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n32 minutes ago, Jimbodiah said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve tried hat, but it only keeps the ship in the same position to a relative body. It does not actively turn the vessel towards it from a certain part\u0027s perspective.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif you\u0027re using a non-tracking solar panel then you\u0027ll have to do the work yourself, and get the probe spinning at the right speed to always be facing the sun while it orbits. For this, Persistent Rotation will indeed do the trick, just not automagically\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jimbodiah","CreatedById":152759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T20:47:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot looking for PR, it\u0027s not a solution I can use. Basically an orientation node like prograde/normal/radial\u00A0but towards the\u00A0sun is what I am looking for.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nertea","CreatedById":83952,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T21:59:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis might be silly, but what about making the Sun your ship\u0027s target and using orient to target as a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E mode?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jimbodiah","CreatedById":152759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T23:15:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGheghe \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0Can\u00A0you even select the sun? \u00A0I\u0027ll try it out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-03T23:15:39Z\u0022 title=\u002211/03/2016 11:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 3, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Jimbodiah\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jenyaza","CreatedById":155707,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-04T17:36:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs I\u00A0know, PR\u00A0allows you to select relative body, even sun.\u00A0Look for any buttons on main window, and press it - new window with this option must appear.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jimbodiah","CreatedById":152759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-07T10:13:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83952-nertea/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283952\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83952-nertea/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nertea\u003C/a\u003E I can\u0027t select the sun, so that will not work. Nice idea though \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155707-jenyaza/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155707\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155707-jenyaza/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Jenyaza\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0This will not turn the vessel to face the sun, it will only keep it in the last position relative to a selected object.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sarbian","CreatedById":57146,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-07T13:11:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMechjeb Smart ASS\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Eklykti","CreatedById":169572,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-07T13:23:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222841864\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151407\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478513583\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jimbodiah\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Jimbodiah said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis will not turn the vessel to face the sun, it will only keep it in the last position relative to a selected object.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you can turn to the sun manually and then set it as a reference body in PR.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-07T13:52:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222841864\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151407\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478513583\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jimbodiah\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Jimbodiah said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t select the sun, so that will not work. Nice idea though \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFYI: the reason for this is that \u0027targeting\u0027 basically means \u0027compare this object\u0027s orbit with my own\u0027. This is what creates the intersection points between the two orbital planes (\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ascending Node\u0022\u003EAN\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Descending Node\u0022\u003EDN\u003C/abbr\u003E), as well as the close approach markers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLogic dictates that it only makes sense to be able to target orbits that are comparable to your own in the first place. In other words, orbits around the same central focus point that you are also in orbit around. Or, to put it differently: anything in the same \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E, except the central focus itself (because that one orbits a different focus, in a different \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs such, because there is no focus for the Sun to orbit around, you can never be in orbit around the same focus as the Sun, and therefore you can never target the Sun in KSP - regardless of where you are. Unless of course you \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/116058-wip121-galactic-neighborhood\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Emod it heavily\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jimbodiah","CreatedById":152759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-07T15:40:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222842002\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151407\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478524306\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257146\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sarbian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, sarbian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMechjeb Smart ASS\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSmart Ass! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E Lol. I will check that, never used that bit beyond pro/retrograde at early career nodes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the helping hands!!! I\u0027m just weird that way sometimes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StarStreak2109","CreatedById":118557,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-08T10:30:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222842122\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151407\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478533238\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jimbodiah\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, Jimbodiah said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSmart Ass! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E Lol. I will check that, never used that bit beyond pro/retrograde at early career nodes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the helping hands!!! I\u0027m just weird that way sometimes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257146\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sarbian\u003C/a\u003E pointed out, use Smart A.S.S., select ADV, then select SUN as Reference and the DOWN as Direction. Then your space craft should face the sun. At least my space crafts do... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jimbodiah","CreatedById":152759,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-08T12:45:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257146\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57146-sarbian/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sarbian\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/118557-starstreak2109/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022118557\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/118557-starstreak2109/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@StarStreak2109\u003C/a\u003E \u00A0Seems to work!!!!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022\u003E \u00A0 Thanks guys!!!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-08T12:46:07Z\u0022 title=\u002211/08/2016 12:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 8, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Jimbodiah\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deimos Rast","CreatedById":157420,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-09T20:58:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyeah, I use MechJeb, but there is also kOS I believe, if you write your own.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}